252 Clarkson Ave., south side, just west of Nostrand Ave., showing house now owned by Mrs. Catherine Iaino, built by Bennett, first florist of Flatbush.

1922.

282 Clarkson Ave., south side, just west from Nostrand Ave., showing the Redgate House, still standing (1936).

1922.

(1) 326 Clarkson Ave., south side, between Nostrand and New York Aves., showing the former Charles E. Koch home. Mr. Koch who was from Rutherford, N. J., was a florist, and occupied this house from 1893 to 1921. The house was in 1922, owned by Latorre and Napolitano. At the present time, (1936), the house is not in existence, and on this site is a garage.

1922.
